# Lumen Analytics environment template.
#
# Copy to `.env.local` for `next dev`, or set these in your container env
# for the deployed demo.

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Portal federation (chunk 4b)
#
# When the Paradigm Portal mints a launch token and redirects to
# `<lumen_base_url>/#portal_token=<JWT>`, the client claims the token by
# POSTing to /api/portal/handoff, which verifies the JWT locally against
# the portal's published JWKS.
#
# - PORTAL_JWKS_URL is the public JWKS document. The portal documents this
#   at /.well-known/jwks.json on its public origin.
# - PORTAL_EXPECTED_ISSUER must match the portal's `iss` claim exactly.
# - PORTAL_EXPECTED_AUD must equal the audience the portal mints for Lumen.
#   Per the contract this is the app slug, which is `lumenanalytics`.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
PORTAL_JWKS_URL=https://portal.projectnexuscode.org/.well-known/jwks.json
PORTAL_EXPECTED_ISSUER=https://portal.projectnexuscode.org
PORTAL_EXPECTED_AUD=lumenanalytics

# Required at boot -- must be 32+ characters
SESSION_SECRET=replace-with-a-real-32-plus-char-random-secret

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Slack alerting (optional)
#
# When set, anomaly triage can route a Block Kit alert to this webhook via
# POST /api/alerts/slack ("Send to Slack" in the anomaly panel, "Send test
# alert" on the Integrations page). Point it at a Slack Incoming Webhook, or
# any HTTPS endpoint, and the payload lands there. When unset the action is a
# no-op that still returns the exact payload it would have sent, so the flow
# stays demonstrable. APP_BASE_URL, when set, becomes the "Open in Lumen"
# button URL inside the alert.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LUMEN_SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL=https://hooks.slack.com/services/T000/B000/XXXX
# APP_BASE_URL=https://lumenanalytics.projectnexuscode.org
